# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for high-risk paths.
#
# SECURITY.md (§Verification, §Controls 6) and ADR-0015 both treat
# CODEOWNERS as the gate on the lab → canonical → fork sync path: changes
# to load-bearing security/CI surfaces must be reviewed by a listed
# identity before merge. This file makes that contract real. Pair it with
# branch protection ("Require review from Code Owners") on `main`.
#
# Last matching pattern wins, so order least-specific → most-specific.

# Default owner for everything not matched by a more specific rule below.
*                               @NeuralEmpowerment

# CI/CD workflows — arbitrary code execution with access to repo secrets.
# A malicious change here can exfiltrate secrets or backdoor every build.
/.github/                       @NeuralEmpowerment

# Harness slot plugins (stack-manager, sensors, hooks, doc-validator, …)
# and the fitness ratchet floors — the eat-own-dogfood security surface.
/harness/                       @NeuralEmpowerment
/harness/sensors/baseline.json  @NeuralEmpowerment

# Observability stack (docker-composed infra) — supply-chain + runtime risk.
/infra/                         @NeuralEmpowerment

# Security standard, hook policy, and agent-plugin config. Changes here
# weaken or strengthen every gate; they must not land unreviewed.
/SECURITY.md                    @NeuralEmpowerment
/security.md                    @NeuralEmpowerment
/lefthook.yml                   @NeuralEmpowerment
/.gitleaksignore                @NeuralEmpowerment
/.claude/                       @NeuralEmpowerment
/CLAUDE.md                      @NeuralEmpowerment
/AGENTS.md                      @NeuralEmpowerment

# Submodule pins — a silently advanced submodule is a supply-chain attack
# vector analogous to GitHub Action tag repointing.
/.gitmodules                    @NeuralEmpowerment
